                           An algorithm is given for the numerical solution of the 'mixed integer' linear programming problem, the problem of maximizing
                              a linear form in finitely many variables constrained both by linear inequalities and the requirement that a proper subset
                              of the variables assume only integral values. The algorithm is an extension of the cutting plane technique for the solution
                              of the 'pure integer' problem. (Author)

